Post Office asked forensic accountants to investigate Horizon IT system in 2012 . 
  Dozens of subpostmasters said they had been wrongly accused of theft, fraud and false accounting . 
  Many were sacked, stripped of savings and even jailed after cash shortfalls were recorded at some branches . 
  Post Office failed to properly investigate why money had gone missing from branches . 
  Report suggests discrepancies could have been caused by computer failures or cyber criminals . 
 